Happy Tuesday Gram! Here‚Äôs another snippet of our workout at @athletetrainingandhealth . 
This triset is great to develop the posterior chain by strengthening your hamstrings and improving knee stability while also focusing on upper body conditioning. 
This is how it works:
1.You will start with 5 reps of BB deadlift with just the bar followed by 10 stability jumps per leg, followed by 10 band pull-aparts.  Without resting, you will go back into the triset and will repeat another round.

2. Now, you will add weights (I added 25 lb x side) and you will do 4 deadlifts followed by 10 stability jumps and 10 band pull-aparts. You will repeat this for 3 rounds without resting and you will keep adding weights to increase resistance.

You are doing 5 total sets and consider the stability hops and band pull-aparts as an active rest. 
A note on the stability hops: these are a great plyometric exercise to develop an explosive and athletic lower body, and to improve your knee stability but you must be aware that improvements in knee stability take time. The longer you have moved poorly, the longer it will take to learn how to move correctly, so be patient!
